Setting up your Mobile App Notification Settings

WhatNew Notification Settings

When You'd Like to Receive Notifications

  • A streamer you follow goes live
  • A stream you've bookmarked goes live
  • Anytime someone @mentions you in a livestream
  • Someone starts following you

Chat Tagging Preferences

You can specify when you'd like to receive notifications for @mentions:

  • Everyone (default): Notified anytime someone tags you in a livestream chat
  • Following only: Only notified when someone you follow tags you in a livestream chat
  • No one: Not notified about @mentions in chat

Note: Users are limited to how many times they can tag you in a given time frame. There are also limits to how many notifications you will receive when you are tagged multiple times in a livestream.

Live Show Settings from Sellers You Follow

Through the seller WhatNew profile, you have the option to select from the below notification preferences:

  • All Notifications: You'll receive a push notification every time the seller goes live
  • Personalized Notifications: You'll receive push notifications for the shows you're likely to open based on past push notification open behavior (default)
  • No Notifications: You won't receive any push notifications when they go live unless you bookmark/save their shows

How to Clear Notifications

To clear the notification icon/badge from the WhatNew app:

  • Clear your DMs in the Activity Tab
  • Clear Notifications in the bell icon
  • You must clear both tabs to clear the badge
